/**
 * Lists all the valid item combinations. Items are combinations via the attachment screen
 * widget. There are 3 main types of combination mechanisms:
 *  1) Attachments - items becomes an attachment in the base item. This is reversible.
 *  2) Merge - one item is merged into another, resulting in a new merged item.
 *  3) Combo merge - "ingredient" items are added as attachments to the base. Once all
 *                   ingredients are present, a combo merge is performed resulting in a
 *                   new item.
 *
 * Fields:
 *  - type: type of item combination. It must be one of:
 *      - ATTACH:     (attach) simply clinging one item onto another
 *      - LAUNCHABLE: (attach) items is mounted as a grenade to be launched
 *      - COMBINE_POINTS:   (merge) items of the same type merged into one slot, combining their status points
 *      - TREAT_ARMOUR:     (merge) applying coating to armours; doesn't care about the status of the attachment
 *      - DESTRUCTION:      (merge) all items disappear on merge
 *      - EXPLOSIVE:        (merge) requires explosives skill check to successfully merge item
 *      - EASY_MERGE:       (merge) no skills check
 *      - ELECTRONIC_MERGE: (merge) requires electronics skill check
 *      - COMBO_MERGE: (combo) merging of multiple items
 *  - baseItem: the internal name of the item being attached to
 *  - item: (attach and merge) the internal name of the item used as attachment
 *  - attachments: (combo only) array (of 2) of internal names ingredient attachment items.
 *  - result: (merge and combo) internal name of the item resulting from the merge
 *  - isExtra: (attach only) if it is available only when the game policy allows extra attachments
 */
